<br>
What's your Top 10 list of hate at your workplace? Here's mine:<br>
<br>
A drive thru bank teller's top ten list:<br>
<br>
10. Please respond to me when I talk to you, I am not an ATM machine, I am flesh and blood and deserve atleast an acknowledgment. Smile, nod, hello, SOMETHING! I hate it when I feel like I am talking to myself!<br>
<br>
9. Don't stuff a wad of cash in my drive up tubes. Crumbled up bills are a pain in the rear, and take longer to count and verify to boot. And they don't like to lay flat in my drawer. One day I'm going to take the cash you're getting back and crumble it into a little wad, and watch you try to stick it in your wallet. And laugh madly when you can't.<br>
<br>
8. I am not responsible for balancing your checkbook. If you have an account, you really should be smart enough to reconcile it yourself. Or, if you can't reconcile it, atleast be able to write your own transactions in your register. I am busy, I don't have time to hold your hand and write everything down for you, I really don't. If you can't do small things for yourself, why in blazes do you even HAVE a checking account? <br>
<br>
7. I'm not stupid. I can distinguish between two transactions. if you have more than one, send all your junk in, and tell me what you need. I'm intelligent enough that if I don't know, I'll ask questions. It's better than playing volleyball with the drive up tube. It annoys the people behind you to no end, then they're grouchy and won't talk to me, because they assume it's my fault!<br>
<br>
6. Your account balance does NOT matter. I don't care if you have 100 grand in your account, I'm not breaking the rules for you. I'm not going to treat you any better than the fool who has 10 bucks in his account. Deal with it...us poor folk do.<br>
<br>
5. Please, please, PLEASE, have your junk ready by the time you get up to my window. I hate &quot;Lane Cloggers&quot;, people who take forever to sign their checks and send em in. Oh, and the math geniuses, who take 20 mins to fill out their deposit slips, and are still wrong. Buy a calculator. <br>
<br>
