<br>
3. Know how much money you're depositing. I wouldn't hand my money over to someone without knowing exactly how much I have! When I ask...how much cash do you have here? I am not stupid, really. I am simply verfiying how much moolah you just handed over to me. Next time I won't ask. And don't ask me where that $20 went...I have no idea.<br>
<br>
2. Yes, our drive up lanes are very narrow. But really, I DIDN'T build the bank. It's not my fault you hit the building because you can't seem to figure out how to drive in the lanes. Don't bitch at me because you feel like an idiot. Drive slowly and cautiously, and you'll make it, I promise. Tons of people do the same every day here, and they make it ok, you can too.<br>
